---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base
  title="Contact — Helix"
  description="Reach the Helix project: commercial licensing and investor inquiries, bug reports and reproductions, or general questions — by email or through GitHub."
>
  <section class="page-hero dark">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="hero-portrait-row">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">contact · questeria</span>
          <h1>One project. <em>One inbox.</em></h1>
          <p class="lede">Helix is built by Questeria (Anthony DeMarco). There is no sales funnel and no support tier — questions, licensing, investment, and bug reports all reach the same person who wrote the 299 bytes at the bottom of the chain.</p>
          <div class="btn-row">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:ajdemarco10@gmail.com">Email the project <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
            <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/anthony-demarco10/" rel="noopener">Connect on LinkedIn</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <img class="hero-portrait" src="/anthony-demarco.jpg" alt="Portrait of Anthony DeMarco, founder of Helix" width="800" height="800" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">Channels</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Pick the door that fits.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="section-lede">Email gets the fastest response for licensing and investment; GitHub keeps technical discussion where the code and the gates live.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card-grid two">
        <a class="link-card" href="mailto:ajdemarco10@gmail.com?subject=Helix%20%E2%80%94%20investor%20%2F%20partnership%20inquiry">
          <span class="lc-kicker">Investors &amp; partners</span>
          <h3>Fund the expansion</h3>
          <p>Helix is raising to fund full-time development: the non-commercial license is intended to be temporary while the project secures investors, early revenue, and industry partners. For investor or partnership conversations, email directly.</p>
          <span class="lc-arrow">ajdemarco10@gmail.com →</span>
        </a>
        <a class="link-card" href="mailto:ajdemarco10@gmail.com?subject=Helix%20%E2%80%94%20commercial%20license">
          <span class="lc-kicker">Commercial licensing</span>
          <h3>Use Helix in your business</h3>
          <p>Any for-profit use needs a separate commercial license today. Describe your use case — internal evaluation, hosted service, product integration — and terms are negotiated directly, without intermediaries.</p>
          <span class="lc-arrow">ajdemarco10@gmail.com →</span>
        </a>
        <a class="link-card" href="https://github.com/Questeria/helix/issues">
          <span class="lc-kicker">Bugs &amp; reproductions</span>
          <h3>Hold the claims to account</h3>
          <p>Found a gate that fails, a hash that doesn't re-derive, or a claim that doesn't trace? Open an issue. The gates are fail-closed on purpose — a real red is information the project wants.</p>
          <span class="lc-arrow">github.com/Questeria/helix/issues →</span>
        </a>
        <a class="link-card" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/anthony-demarco10/" rel="noopener">
          <span class="lc-kicker">Everything else</span>
          <h3>LinkedIn</h3>
          <p>General questions, press, introductions, or anything that doesn't fit the boxes above — connect directly with Anthony DeMarco on LinkedIn, or just use the email.</p>
          <span class="lc-arrow">linkedin.com/in/anthony-demarco10 →</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="notice" style="margin-top: 28px;">
        <p class="notice-title">What to include</p>
        <p>For licensing or investment: who you are, what you want to build or back, and your timeline. For technical reports: your platform, the exact command, and the output — every gate prints enough to diagnose from a paste.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta dark">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Before you write</span>
      <h2>See it run first.</h2>
      <p>The verified GPT-2 and SmolLM2 runs, the proof dashboard, and the one-command reproduction answer most first questions better than email can.</p>
      <div